Parliament, Wednesday 12 June 2019 – Parliament’s Presiding Officers, led by the National Assembly Speaker Ms Thandi Modise and National Council of Provinces Chairperson Mr Amos Masondo, will provide details about all aspects of the 6th Parliament’s State of readiness to host the State of the Nation Address (SONA) by the Head of State. The 20 June SONA is the first for the 6th Parliament of the Republic of South Africa.
	
	Media wishing to attend the briefing session should contact the following Media Relations officials: DETAILS OF THE MEDIA BRIEFING ARE AS FOLLOWS: DATE: THURSDAY, 13 JUNE 2019
	TIME: 13.00
	VENUE: G26, GROUND FLOOR – NATIONAL ASSEMBLY BUILDING, PARLIAMENT ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA
	Enquiries: Moloto Mothapo 082 370 6930 The copy of an Act of Parliament signed by the President is the official version of that Act and is given to the Constitutional Court for safekeeping.Read more